    "name": {
      "value": "Staff of Dunamancy"
    },
    "source": {
      "value": "egw"
    },
    "description": {
      "value": "This staff of polished gray wood bears numerous runes carved along its length. The staff has 10 charges and regains 1d6 + 4 expended charges daily at dawn. If you expend the last charge, roll a d20. On a 1, the staff turns into dust and is destroyed.\n\nWhile holding the staff, you can use an action to expend 2 or more of its charges to cast one of the following spells from it, using your spell save DC and spell attack bonus: fortune\u2019s favor (2 charges), pulse wave (3 charges), or gravity sinkhole (4 charges).\n\nNew Possibility: If you are holding the staff and fail a saving throw against a spell that targets only you, you can turn your failed save into a successful one. This property can\u2019t be used again until the next dawn."
    },
